title: For Sale:  Foam Beds for shooting.
postcontent:
Company has large foam beds measuring about 
84" in length and 40" in width.
Anywhere from 10 inches thick up to 3 Ft in thickness.
Great for Bow and arrow or cross bow shooting.
Has been shot with small handgun calibers. 9mm .380 .22 LR.
Does catch most bullets. 
One bed was cut into a square about 42" x 42" x 18" and shot with 
45 ACP 12 Gauge .40 cal and bullets went straight through. 
However this was done inside of a gun range and distance was pretty close.
May hold up to bigger calibers if shot through a complete bun and at a farther distance.
I will sell two large buns for 100. I have several you can choose from with different thicknesses. Some are very soft similar to memory foam. Others are extremely hard.
Each bun weights roughly 200 - 250 lbs. Two on a pallet is about 500lbs.
We have shot several times with a Crossbow and it holds up great. 
Bolt will not enter completely. Very easy to cut if you have a hot wire or the correct tools to do so. Have tried to take a hand saw to cut samples off and it is very difficult.
It's hard to explain the texture and feeling on the material. If you are interested you can come by and take a look at the materials and feel them for your self. 
When shot it does not chip off and leave a mess. However I am sure after being abused and shot for a while it will begin to tear but to my opinion it will take quite a lot of abuse before that happening.

If interested we have them stored at a warehouse with a forklift for easy loading in a truck. 

Give me a call at REDACTED to set up a time to take a look. If i don't answer PLEASE leave a message and I will return the call as soon as possible. I get a lot of calls from customers due to work. 
Text for a quicker response.

Or Email and I will answer right away.

Thanks,

Alex.

 If a federally imposed gun ban is put in place that prohibits the sale of an AR-15 from a manufacturer or a dealer to a customer, it will prevent any further transfers of AR-15’s. title: For Sale:  FINAL $$ REDUCTION! Thompson Sub-machine Gun - DEMILITARIZED
postcontent:
THIS IS NOT A FIREARM. IT WILL NOT FIRE AND CANNOT BE MADE TO FIRE. IT IS A NON-FUNCTIONAL PIECE OF HISTORY THAT IS NOT PROHIBITED BY ANY RULES.

 This is a magnificent display gun built from excellent WWII Thompson M-1928 parts and reassembled with a fantastic non-functioning new made anodized aluminum display receiver. Every part on this display gun is original WW2 manufactured other than the receiver. Original WW2 parts include:

• Detachable Walnut Butt Stock
• Complete Lower Frame Assembly
• Walnut Pistol Grip
• Barrel
• Sling and Buttstock Oiler
• Walnut Horizontal Foregrip
• 30 Round Magazine

 The Thompson 1928 sub machine gun is perhaps the most recognizable firearm of World War II, made famous by the Airborne Troops of the 101st and 82nd Airborne Divisions. This military model differs from the original commercial model in its horizontal foregrip. Though heavy by today's standards, the weight helped control the .45 caliber bursts when operated on full automatic.

 The Thompson submachine was invented by John T. Thompson in 1919 and became infamous during the Prohibition era. It was a common sight at the time, being used by both law enforcement officers and criminals. The Thompson was also known informally as: the "Tommy Gun," the "Chicago Typewriter" and the "Chopper." The Thompson was favored by soldiers, criminals and police alike for its ergonomics, compactness, large .45 ACP cartridges, and high volume of automatic fire and among civilian collectors for its historical significance.

 Many new made replica and Airsoft Thompsons flood the market today, but this is an opportunity to own a true piece of history, a genuine WW2 Thompson in excellent condition and totally legal to own in the USA by federal law without any type of license.

 The following link provides further insight, pictures and online pricing:

http://www.ima-usa.com/nation/u-s-militaria/u-s-machine-guns/thompson-smg/original-wwii-thompson-m1928-display-smg.html

Burris 3-9x40mm Fullfield II Rifle Scope w/ Burris 10x32mm Landmark Binoculars gives you a full spot-and-shoot package! This value package from Burris includes the Burris 3x-9x 40mm Fullfield-II Riflescope and the Burris Landmark 10x32mm Binoculars.

The Burris Fullfield II Rifle Scope has a one-piece main tube and eyepiece, Burris envied steel-on-steel adjustment system, and HiLume multi-coatings on every single air to glass lens surface. The Burris FullField-II Scope is even more forgiving for eye position, is a little shorter, and a good bit lighter. The magnification ring and eyepiece have been made into one solid unit requiring only two seals rather than three. To change magnification, simply turn the entire eyepiece. Burris Fullfield 2 Scope eliminated most of the potential leak paths in the eyepiece/power ring area and sealed the remainder with special quad seals instead of O-rings. The adjustment system has been moved to improve mounting options and the European-style adjustable eyepiece requires no locking mechanism. The Ballistic Plex reticle has a lower vertical crosshair with small ballistic lines that automatically compensate for bullet drop from 100 to 500 yards for many common cartridges. The Burris Fullfield-2 Riflescope is lighter, better sealed, and has a relocated adjustment system compared to the original Burris Fullfield.

The Burris Landmark Binoculars combine light weight, fully coated lenses and water resistant, fogproof construction. These Burris Binoculars also include a tough rubber armor coating and twist-up eyecups. Top all this off with a neck strap, carrying case, a full year warranty and a very affordable price and you have yourself a synonym for optical value.

Waterproof: All Burris optics are proven to be absolutely waterproof. Each scope is submerged in water with a temperature of 50° C. The extremely hot water transfers its heat to the scope and the internal nitrogen expends 100% testing assures quality. Each scope is filled and purged at least 24 times with high quality, laboratory grade dry nitrogen. Each nitrogen cycle absorbs airborne and residual surface moisture that is evacuated from the scope. Burris uses specially made quad seals to provide double insurance against leakage.
Fog proof: The nitrogen contained in the scope is of high quality (ultra dry, laboratory grade nitrogen), ultra pure and ultra clean. To be sure that all airborne moisture and surfaces moisture within a scope is evacuated, testing consists of 24 cycles of pressurizing the scope and then subjecting it to a vacuum. The tests are both cost & time intensive.
Shock proof: Burris scopes are subjected to extreme recoil tests. An impact machine is used to measure and duplicate the recoil pulse acceleration and duration. This machine has been calibrated and verified by an independent laboratory to replicate the wave frequencies and shock impulses that a scope is subjected to.
Ballistic Plex reticle - with a basic crosshair reticle, calculating hold-over is a mix of art, science and just plain luck, which is why Burris developed the Ballistic Plex reticle. The key is the copyrighted lower vertical crosshair. With most common hunting cartridges, a shooter can use the reticle to compensate for bullet drop and aim dead-on at targets from 100 to 500 yards out. The need for hold-over guesstimation is eliminated. Using it is simple. Start by sighting-in your rifle at 100 or 200 yards at your scope's highest magnification.
